      </div>
      <div class="msgContentFrame">Job adjustments and stuff aside, just some basic play mechanics I think need adjusted due to the raise in level cap and the changing size in the player base: <br /> <br /><li>Merging more servers - yeah it can suck, but there's generally less than 1000 people on and if there's more than 10 people seeking party (all level ranges) that seems busy anymore. There are some advantages to having less people on, but generally more disadvantages since you need people to do stuff. </li> <br /><li>Merge the AH (ie the 3 towns and Jeuno), lower the fees, allow more items to be put up there. Also due to lack of people, I think convenience is the main issue here, browsing bazaars is annoying, if its not EX it should be able to go on the AH. The starter cities are just dead, why waste 5 minutes either warping or muling to Jeuno because you need something.</li> <br /><li>Requiring X number of people to do an event, I'm thinking assault/salvage here, and certain campaign ops. Its just obnoxious, also exasperated by the number of people on at a given time. </li>  <br /> <br /><li>A reason for people to actually do campaign. I don't know what, but I'd like to complete all the ops (like I completed all the assaults), that task seems impossible since it seems unlikely that my server would ever conquer certain zones again.</li>  <br /> <br /><div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><a href="HTTP://code.google.com/p/ffxidmgformula/" rel="external nofollow" title="code.google.com/p/ffxidmgformula/">FFIX Melee Damage Comparitor</a> <br /><a href="HTTP://www.ffxiah.com/player.php?id=458269" rel="external nofollow" title="www.ffxiah.com/player.php?id=458269">Brimstone</a></div></div>
