      <div class="msgContentFrame">Level cooking? Costs about 1, maybe 2 million gil to get to 100 with relevant subs. Takes about 3 days buying all your stuff from NPC and selling the results right back to NPC. Sure there's people that can't afford that, but you spent god knows how much on PW's H2H for your PUP, are you trying to tell me you couldn't find 2 million gil in between selling all that Salvage gear? <br /> <br />edit - As far as balance is concerned, I agree. I think what the new team is doing right now is trying to make the game fun for everybody again. At the moment that means ignoring certain glaring issues, like the fact that pet jobs still suck and a couple DDs have been completely left behind as far as damage and/or utility is concerned. However if you look at some of the changes they are making, it's all stuff that we have been asking for since 2005. There's a huge list of complaints about this game that SE never even responded to, it takes time to adjust those things and implement new systems. The fact that they have so quickly made some of these changes shows that they somebody was paying attention all these years, even if it wasn't the people in charge. We have at least two more big updates before we hit 99, and that's where it makes sense to balance things out. Right now SE is dazzling us with fun and exciting stuff, while patching up things that should have and could have been fixed years ago. Lets make the basic game functional, then worry about balance. <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Nov 20th 2010 12:02pm by TybudX </span></i><div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Dooom wrote:</div><div class="orig">BG elitists &lt;3 haste. <br /> <br />Allatards/uber casuals hate elitists. <br /> <br />Allatards/uber casuals hate haste, as valuing it would acknowledge that elitists are right</div></div> <br /> <br /><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">kerbero